(1) The Minister or, with the approval of the Minister, a local authority , may— (a) establish markets; (b) provide all such matters and things as may be necessary for the convenient use of the market; (c) take stallages, rents, fees and tolls in respect of the use by any person of any market; (d) demolish, reconstruct, abolish, close or move, any market; and (e) appoint inspectors of markets.
